.TH "echo_erase_tab" 9 "echo_erase_tab" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
echo_erase_tab \- add operation to erase a tab
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" echo_erase_tab
.BI "(unsigned int num_chars "  ","
.BI "int after_tab "  ","
.BI "struct n_tty_data *ldata "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "num_chars" 12
number of character columns already used
.IP "after_tab" 12
true if num_chars starts after a previous tab
.IP "ldata" 12
n_tty data

Add an operation to the echo buffer to erase a tab.

Called by the eraser function, which knows how many character
columns have been used since either a previous tab or the start
of input.  This information will be used later, along with
canon column (if applicable), to go back the correct number
of columns.
